---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About Me | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				{AboutHeroImage && (
					<div class="hero-image">
						<img src={AboutHeroImage.src} alt="" />
					</div>
				)}
				<div class="prose">
					<div class="title">
						<h1>About Me</h1>
						<hr />
					</div>
					<p>
						I’m an IT Specialist focused on infrastructure, cloud, and automation, with hands-on experience managing and 
						optimizing systems at scale. Currently, I work at TUI Group, where I support and maintain enterprise environments,
						managing hundreds of endpoints and ensuring reliability across critical services.
					</p>

					<p>
						My work sits at the intersection of operations and engineering. I’m particularly interested in building systems 
						that are not only functional, but maintainable, reproducible, and secure. This includes automating infrastructure 
						with tools like Ansible, designing clean network architectures, and implementing practical solutions that reduce 
						operational overhead while improving resilience.
					</p>

					<p>
						Before joining TUI, I gained experience in both structured enterprise environments and smaller, fast-paced teams.
						At Yamaha Motor Canada, I worked as a System Support Analyst, focusing on endpoint management, troubleshooting, 
						and IT operations within a corporate environment. Later, at San Franchise, I took on a broader role, handling 
						infrastructure, web systems, and general IT responsibilities, which strengthened my ability to work across multiple
						domains and adapt quickly.
					</p>

					<p>
						Outside of my professional role, I actively build and document infrastructure projects in my homelab. This environment 
						allows me to experiment with technologies such as Linux server administration, containerization, reverse proxy 
						architectures, and cloud integrations. I focus on real-world scenarios—secure remote access, backup strategies, 
						monitoring, and automation—treating these projects as production-like systems rather than simple experiments.
					</p>

					<p>
						I’m currently expanding my expertise in cloud architecture and infrastructure as code, with a particular focus on
						AWS and Terraform. My goal is to deepen my ability to design scalable, reliable systems and transition further 
						into cloud-focused engineering roles.
					</p>

					<p>
						This website serves as a central hub for my work—bringing together my blog, technical documentation, and projects. 
						I aim to share practical insights, clear architectural thinking, and lessons learned from building and operating 
						systems in real environments.
					</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
		<style>
			main {
				width: calc(100% - 2em);
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 3em 1em;
			}
			.hero-image {
				width: 100%;
			}
			.hero-image img {
				display: block;
				margin: 0 auto;
				border-radius: 12px;
				box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
			}
			.prose {
				padding: 1em;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.title {
				margin-bottom: 1em;
				padding: 1em 0;
				text-align: center;
				line-height: 1;
			}
			.title h1 {
				margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
			}
			hr {
				border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
